	<text>
		<body>
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001033_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 12 top left--><!--hand 02 68010 superscript A top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">30<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May 1857</p>
<lb/><p><persName>Lady Eastlake</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I am both 
<lb/>ashamed and sorry 
<lb/>on account of 
<lb/>having entirely 
<lb/>forgotten your 
<lb/>most kind 
<lb/>invitation for 
<lb/>Wednesday last 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001033_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>I was employed 
<lb/>during the greater 
<lb/>part of last week 
<lb/>in trying to get 
<lb/>away from the 
<lb/>bustle of London, 
<lb/>then the beginning 
<lb/>of this, was spent 
<lb/>in removing from 
<lb/>town to <placeName>Hadley 
<lb/>Green</placeName>, and the 
<lb/>privilege you had 
<lb/>most obligingly 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001033_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>placed within my 
<lb/>reach, of meeting 
<lb/>the <persName>Bishop of 
<lb/>London</persName> and the 
<lb/><persName>Editor of the Times</persName>, 
<lb/>never once flitted 
<lb/>across my mind 
<lb/>until <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName>
<lb/>enquired the reason 
<lb/>of my absence 
<lb/>this morning.</p>
<lb/><p>If <persName>your Ladyship</persName><del type="strikethrough">s</del>
<lb/>says "Well he does 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001033_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/>not deserve my 
<lb/>consideration, or notice" <!--closing quotation marks on image of page 1-->
<lb/>I cannot say a 
<lb/>word in my 
<lb/>defence. I only 
<lb/>confess my fault 
<lb/>without any 
<lb/>attempt to justify 
<lb/>myself, and though 
<lb/>you may never 
<lb/>forgive me I shall 
<lb/>I shall never be able to 
<lb/>blame anyone for 
<lb/>it but myself. I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">David Livingstone</p>
			
